<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Use</h2>

  <p>
    Use adjustable support hooks, like roller systems, if you’re growing indeterminate tomatoes in a greenhouse or long season. They make plant management easier as growth continues.
  </p>

  <p>
    If your season or setup is limited, simple fixed hooks can still work effectively.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Plan for how tall your plants will actually get.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Bottom Line</h2>

  <p>
    The best support hooks for indeterminate tomatoes are those that match your growing conditions and allow you to manage continuous vine growth.
  </p>

  <p>
    For most gardeners, adjustability becomes more important as the season progresses.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Growth doesn’t stop — your system shouldn’t either.
  </p>
